snippet.textDisplay:
I must have listened to this 100 times since it was released, for several reasons.

It reminds me of my Dad. He always would put on "trip tapes" which were music to animated videos. I feel like my Dad knows some sort of celestial secret.

The music is beautiful. Julian's voice is always great and the story it tells is stunning. It is the story of us. How we cause hurt and evil to each other and destroy the Earth and that the end of us will come and the Earth will become a paradise again.

Something I often think about is how "Earth" is an anagram of heart and the Earth gives us life. Stop taking it for granted.

snippet.textDisplay: This is song about a coming apocalyptic or (reset) event that will likely kill most people on earth, and the “other side” is the mythical land of Shambhala - which plays a role in the continuity of human races during and after extinction level events. Many prophecies say that children are central to the prophecy, similar to the movie Knowing. Lots of music videos, movies, and TV shows have been depicting the same events in this music video. “At the door” means “at the door between the old world and the “new world” , the door being an apocalyptic event (solar flare). The prophecy says that many things lose order in the days and weeks leading up to the event. This song is not about cancer or the lead singer.
